## Problem

`summarizeChunks` in `src/agents/compaction.ts` processes message chunks sequentially, building a progressive summary. If chunk N succeeds but chunk N+1 fails after exhausting 3 retries, the exception propagates up and the partial summary from chunks 0..N is lost.

The caller `summarizeWithFallback` catches the error and falls back, but it doesn't have access to the partial summary. This means a transient provider failure on the last chunk discards all summarization work from previous chunks.

## Fix

Track `lastSuccessful` inside the loop. On non-abort/non-timeout failure after retry exhaustion, return the partial summary instead of propagating the error. Abort and timeout errors still propagate immediately since those indicate intentional cancellation.

## Real behavior proof
Behavior addressed: mid-chain chunk summarization failures now return the partial summary from successfully processed chunks instead of losing all progress.
Real environment tested: local source checkout of openclaw/openclaw at commit 71b79f008d (current upstream/main) on Linux x86_64, Node v26.0.0.
Exact steps or command run after this patch: pnpm tsgo:core (type check); reviewed the error handling flow through summarizeChunks, summarizeWithFallback, and the compaction-safeguard retry loop.
Evidence after fix: type check output and code diff below.

```
$ pnpm tsgo:core
$ node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core.tsbuildinfo
```
No errors.

Before (chunk failure loses all progress):
```typescript
for (const chunk of chunks) {
    summary = await retryAsync(() => generateSummary(...), { attempts: 3, ... });
}
return summary ?? DEFAULT_SUMMARY_FALLBACK;
```

After (chunk failure returns partial summary):
```typescript
let lastSuccessful = summary;
for (const chunk of chunks) {
    try {
        summary = await retryAsync(() => generateSummary(...), { attempts: 3, ... });
        lastSuccessful = summary;
    } catch (err) {
        if (isAbortError(err) || isTimeoutError(err)) throw err;
        log.warn("chunk summarization failed after retries; returning partial summary", { err });
        return lastSuccessful ?? DEFAULT_SUMMARY_FALLBACK;
    }
}
```

Observed result after fix: type check passes. Abort/timeout errors still propagate. Non-abort failures return the best partial summary available.
What was not tested: actual multi-chunk compaction with a mid-chain provider failure (would require a running OpenClaw instance with a large enough context to produce multiple chunks, then injecting a provider failure after the first chunk succeeds).
